message:
Very good article for well understanding the Await process. I am working in WinRT device and I follow your MSDN article [https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/dn605875.aspx](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/dn605875.aspx)  
for binding my control in MVVM way.   
Somethime I need to be called back make some data manipulation before updating the binding properties. I try adding to your NotifyTaskCompletion class another constructor with an optional Action parameter to be able to add a callback function. That work great, except that the callback function call the raiseproperty from another thread (not UI thread). I try to add:

 Window.Current.Dispatcher.RunAsync(CoreDispatcherPriority.Normal, () =>  
 {  
if (Connection.IsCompleted && !Connection.IsFaulted)  
titre = "Logged user - " + _settings.Values["userName"];

 });

but nothing is updted (no crash no exception). Any suggestion?
